**`landing_page_updated`** is emitted alongside `landing_page_changed`
(page:update) when the admin swaps the landing page. The config:update
channel drives UI elements like the "Landing Page" badge in CustomPages
and triggers a fallback `refresh()` in PageBuilder for edge cases where
the page:update WS push was missed.

### Page Actions (`page:update`)

| `action`               | `data`             | Delivery                          |
| ---------------------- | ------------------ | --------------------------------- |
| `page_created`         | PageBuilderPage    | broadcast                         |
| `page_updated`         | PageBuilderPage    | broadcast (except sender)         |
| `page_deleted`         | `{ id, slug }`     | broadcast                         |
| `landing_page_changed` | PageBuilderPage    | broadcast (full new landing page) |
| `landing_updated`      | `LandingSection[]` | broadcast                         |

**`landing_page_changed`** is emitted by `setLandingPage` via `hub.BroadcastPage`.
It carries the full enriched page so clients can swap the landing page via
WebSocket with zero HTTP requests, completely bypassing CDN caches.

**`page_updated`** uses `BroadcastPageExceptUser` — the sender already has the
authoritative page from the HTTP response, so they don't receive their own
update back. All other clients receive it and apply via `applyIncomingData`.

### Notification Actions

Notifications arrive as raw `AppNotification` objects via the `notification`
message type. Read/delete state is synchronized via a `notification:sync`
message on auth connection and `notification:read` for individual or bulk
read/delete events during a session.

| Message type        | Payload                       | Delivery                 |
| ------------------- | ----------------------------- | ------------------------ |
| `notification`      | AppNotification               | direct push              |
| `notification:sync` | `{ unread_count: number }`    | direct push (on connect) |
| `notification:read` | `{ action, id? }` — see below | direct push              |

`notification:read` actions:

- `read` — `{ id }` — single notification marked read
- `deleted` — `{ id }` — single notification deleted
- `all_read` — no id — all notifications marked read
- `all_deleted` — no id — all notifications deleted

