## Backend Hub API

All hub interaction in service/handler code goes through these methods on `*ws.Hub`:

| Method                                             | Delivery mode                    | Use for                                     |
| -------------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------- |
| `hub.Broadcast(msg)`                               | all clients                      | Store catalog, site config, page edits      |
| `hub.PropagateUser(userID, data)`                  | `user:{id}` subs                 | User profile mutations                      |
| `hub.PropagateForumCategories(id, data, action)`   | `forum_category:{id}`            | Category mutations                          |
| `hub.PropagateForumThread(id, data, action)`       | `thread:{id}`                    | Thread + comment mutations                  |
| `hub.PropagateInboxConversation(id, data, action)` | `inbox_conversation:{id}`        | DM messages                                 |
| `hub.PropagateStoreProduct(id, data, action)`      | `store_product:{id}`             | (reserved; use Broadcast for catalog)       |
| `hub.BroadcastStoreCatalog(data, action)`          | all clients                      | Store CRUD events (all uses today)          |
| `hub.SendToUser(userID, msg)`                      | direct (all sessions for userID) | Notifications, cart sync, purchase outcomes |
| `hub.PropagateToAll(resourceType, data, action)`   | all matching-prefix subs         | Bulk subscription fan-out                   |

`hub.SendToUser` must be implemented if not already present. Signature:

```go
func (h *Hub) SendToUser(userID int64, msg *Message)
```

Iterates `h.clients`, matches `c.UserID == userID`, enqueues `msg` to `c.Send`.

