## Reconnect Invariants

1. The reconnect timer fires after 3 s on any `onclose` or `onerror`.
2. On `ws.onopen`, the full `subscriptionsRef` Set is replayed so no
   subscription is silently lost.
3. Auth state changes (login/logout) close and re-open the socket so the
   new JWT is used on the next connection. Permission-only token refreshes
   do NOT disconnect — the token is patched in-place via atom update only.
4. Components that hold stale REST-loaded data across reconnects MUST add a
   `socketAtom` dependency useEffect that re-runs the initial load when the
   `socket` value changes (same guard as `Store.tsx`):

```typescript
const socket = useAtomValue(socketAtom);
const socketMounted = useRef(false);
useEffect(() => {
  if (!socketMounted.current) {
    socketMounted.current = true;
    return;
  }
  if (socket) loadData(); // re-fetch on reconnect
}, [socket, loadData]);
```

